Money Stuff =0A Actually this is a greenwashing case: US prosecutors charge=
d Gautam Adani =0Awith helping drive a $250 million bribery scheme, in a st=
unning bl =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click=3Fs=3D825881=
&stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D11787228&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233be620525&p=3D1121=
2024>=0A=0A=0A=0AAdani=0A=0AActually this is a greenwashing case <>:=0A=0AU=
S prosecutors charged Gautam Adani with helping drive a $250 million briber=
y =0Ascheme, in a stunning blow to India=E2=80=99s most powerful businessma=
n and close ally =0Aof Prime Minister Narendra Modi.=0A=0AFederal prosecuto=
rs alleged on Wednesday that Adani, one of the world=E2=80=99s =0Arichest p=
eople, and other defendants promised to pay more than $250 million in =0Abr=
ibes to Indian government officials to win solar energy contracts, and =0Ac=
oncealed the plan as they sought to raise money from US investors. US law =
=0Aallows federal prosecutors to pursue foreign corruption allegations if t=
hey =0Ainvolve certain links to American investors or markets.=0A=0AHere ar=
