rm of high-grade and junk-rated bonds as well as a subordinated equity tran=
che, in exchange receiving a share of the interest and principal payments f=
rom the assets in the fund.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Buying the vehi=
cles lets insurers sharply reduce the money they must set aside to back the=
ir exposure to the private credit fund, since US insurance industry rules a=
pply capital charges of 30% or more to holdings of fund shares, compared to=
 low-to-mid single digits for most debt.</p></blockquote><p style=3D"margin=
: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CFund shares=E2=80=9D are, categorically, risky, so they=
